
[1]impious

   IM'PIOUS, a. [L. impius; in and pius, pious.]

   1. Irreverent towards the Supreme Being; wanting in veneration for God
   and his authority; irreligious; profane. The scoffer at God and his
   authority is impious. The profane swear is impious.

   When vice prevails and impious men bear sway,

   The post of honor is a private station.

   2. Irreverent towards God; proceeding from or manifesting a contempt
   for the Supreme Being; tending to dishonor God or his laws,and bring
   them into contempt; as an impious deed; impious language; impious
   writings.
